  "application_type": "All Other",
  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - Insufficient information has been provided to demonstrate that the single storey buildings on the site are used for purposes within Class E of the Use Classes Order 2020 and it would consequently not be possible to retain the use of the buildings as Class E. ",
    "Reason : 2 - Insufficient information has been provided to demonstrate that the use of the single storey buildings under flexible Class E use would provide for an identified need, contribute to the area strategy for Nine Elms and meet the needs of the building occupants, contrary to policies LP17, LP34, LP35, LP37 and LP54. Insufficient information has also been provided to demonstrate that the flexible Class E use would have an acceptable impact on neighbouring occupants in terms of transport, including servicing and deliveries; waste management; of noise; disturbance; pollution; and odour, contrary to the Local Plan policies LP1, LP2, LP14, LP51. ",
    "Reason : 3 - The design, materials and appearance of the development does not accord with the principles of Local Plan policies LP1 and LP3 as it does not provide a high quality detailed design that enhances and relates positively to the character of the area including the setting of the Battersea Park conservation area, which would be contrary to Local Plan polices LP1, LP2 and LP3.",
    "Reason : 4 - The proposal fails to adequately address and mitigate flood risk, contrary to the requirements of the National Planning Policy Framework and Local Plan policy LP12. "
  ],
